race.comment: Strong contest to end the day. WILLIE OPPA (8) attacked the line strongly first-up when a respectable fifth over 1550m at Canterbury. Key jockey change from the low gate and has a solid second-up record. MURPHILLY (12) gave a good account of himself at start thirteen when a slashing Maiden winner over this course and trip. Comes here in peak condition and Grant Buckley stays in the saddle. Go close. LIBERTY PARK (2) handy gelding capable on his day. Returned over the unsuitable trip from the outside gate when a poor eleventh over 1300m at Rosehill in BM72 class. Has won second-up and will relish the claim and 1600m. Keep safe. UPWARDLY MOBILE (5) scored a well-deserved victory when she launched late for a dominant win over 1600m at Newcastle. Gets map favours with the rise in weight. Stays in the mix.
